# Documentation Guidelines

All markdown files (`docs/`, `README.md`, skill files, rule descriptions) must follow `docs/documentation-guidelines.md`.

## Key Rules

- Use active voice — never passive ("the lexer reads the file," not "the file is read by the lexer")
- Prefer bullet points or numbered lists over dense paragraphs
- Keep sentences short — one idea per sentence, one idea per bullet point
- Remove filler words: "basically," "simply," "just," "actually," "really"
- Lead with "what" and "why" before "how"
- Write for someone reading the document for the first time
